1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:02,944
Delegation does not remove human judgment.

2
00:00:02,894 --> 00:00:06,028
It changes where judgment creates the most value.

3
00:00:06,028 --> 00:00:12,538
Low-risk actions such as reading, searching, drafting, and preparing can usually run with wider autonomy.

4
00:00:12,538 --> 00:00:20,269
High-impact actions such as sending, paying, deleting, changing production, or making a public claim should receive narrower permissions.

5
00:00:20,269 --> 00:00:27,384
Place human approval immediately before an irreversible action, after the agent has prepared the evidence needed for a fast decision.

6
00:00:27,384 --> 00:00:33,625
Do not require approval for every harmless read, and do not wait until after a damaging action to review it.

7
00:00:33,625 --> 00:00:36,625
Review capacity is also a real bottleneck.

8
00:00:36,625 --> 00:00:43,644
If an agent produces ten times more work but the output remains difficult to inspect, total productivity may not improve.

9
00:00:43,644 --> 00:00:46,903
Design acceptance criteria before execution.

10
00:00:46,903 --> 00:00:53,365
Ask for a diff, a checklist, a reconciliation report, citations, test results, or a preview.

11
00:00:53,365 --> 00:00:59,951
The best review artifact makes important failures obvious without forcing the human to reconstruct the entire process.

12
00:00:59,951 --> 00:01:02,461
Split the work where the risk changes.

13
00:01:02,461 --> 00:01:05,759
Research and drafting can be one automated stage.

14
00:01:05,759 --> 00:01:08,942
External sending can be a separate approval stage.

15
00:01:08,942 --> 00:01:14,230
Data transformation can run automatically while deletion of source records remains prohibited.

16
00:01:14,230 --> 00:01:20,673
Add stopping conditions for missing context, repeated failure, budget limits, and ambiguous outcomes.

17
00:01:20,673 --> 00:01:25,567
An agent that knows when to stop is more useful than one that always claims to finish.

18
00:01:25,567 --> 00:01:27,105
Chapter recap.

19
00:01:27,105 --> 00:01:33,105
First, give wider autonomy to reversible preparation and narrower authority to irreversible action.

20
00:01:33,105 --> 00:01:38,153
Second, define acceptance evidence before execution so review stays tractable.

21
00:01:38,153 --> 00:01:43,298
Third, stop on missing context, repeated failure, or ambiguous completion.
